This looks a bit excessive. Isn't this enough?
```suggestion
     * @var PathsHelper&\PHPUnit\Framework\MockObject\MockObject
```

But I'd suggest to use the real services instead of the mock and set the `cache_path` param in the `setUp` method to what you need. This could be a simple functional test extending `MauticMysqlTestCase`. It will test all the real services together so we'll really know if it works. You can then remove the whole `getCommandTester` method and simplify the test considerably.

Example:
```php
public function setUp(): void
    {
        $this->configParams['cache_path']  = __DIR__.'/resource/cache/tmp';

        parent::setUp();
    }
```

